author: HILARY MOSS
title: 9 Models to Watch This Season
text: 9 Models to Watch This Season By Hilary Moss Ahead of the fall/winter 2017 shows, T and the casting director Arianna Pradarelli round up the runway’s most intriguing fresh faces — some making their New York Fashion Week debuts, others a few seasons in. Wallette Watson 21, N.C. Image Originally from Raleigh, the now New York-based Watson walked at Yeezy and Coach 1941 last season and in Paris for labels like Saint Laurent, Christian Dior, Valentino and Sonia Rykiel. For fall/winter 2017, expect to see her in London and Milan as well. (Her favorite way to pass the time backstage, she notes, is with a deck of cards.) “If I weren’t modeling, I would be singing — working on an album, and in the studio day and night,” she says. “I think I started singing when I came out of the womb!” Her talents also include dancing — she was classically trained in ballet. “Being your own amazingly beautiful self is what sets you apart from everyone else,” Watson adds, “no matter what anyone says.”
